a - add data to buffer

c - clean data in buffer

q - quit from editor (if you save of clean data from buffer)

p - print data in buffer

w - write data to file (requires an option(filename): w test.txt)

wa - append data to file (reqires an option(filename): wa test.txt)

pf - print filename (show the data in global variable for filename)

sf - set filename (set the filename in global variable, that uses 
this commands: w, wa, pf)
special behaviour: (if global variable is set, you can omit the 
filename as an argument in this commands: w, wa, pf)

sp - set prompt

fb - fill buffer (put the filename as an argument or set the filename
using sf command)

